Plz check my problem? I have made a program 4 sequential search->
#include<stdio.h>
int sequential(int*,int,int);
int main()
{
int i=12;
int a[]={1,4,2,5,6,3,7,8};
i=sequential(a,i,8);
if(i==-1)
printf("not found");
else
printf("%d found",i);;
return 0;
}
int sequential(int *a,int s,int n)
{int i;
a[8]=s;//Problem
for(i=0;i<=n;i++)
printf("%d ",a);
for(i=0;a!=s;i++);
return i<n?i:-1;
}

in that program i make an array of 8(0-7)in length I have assign seach element(s) in a[n](n=8).According to me it should give segmentation fault but it runs perfactly.Even if I assign search element in a[9] or a[10] etc,it doesnot give any error and executes perfactly.I am not able to get why it executes error free.Please explain it to me. 
